      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This unit maintains factory-spec compression across all chambers and operates with a seamless transition between primary and secondary boost phases. The five-speed manual transmission provides crisp engagement, paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis is impeccably preserved, retaining its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and lightweight aluminum components. Finished in collector-grade paint with a pristine interior, this FD is free of the common 'sticky dash' or bolster wear. It remains a mechanically stock, thermally-optimized example of 90s performance engineering.",
